1
00:00:07,240 --> 00:00:09,760
Behold the mighty cockroach.

2
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:15,880
Believed to have originated
in the Silurian period...

3
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:18,960
over 350 million years ago.

4
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:21,680
They can be found in
every part of the world,

5
00:00:21,760 --> 00:00:24,760
from the tropics
to the arctic.

6
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:28,080
There exists
4,000 known species,

7
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:30,080
and in a year,

8
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:35,320
a single female can produce
over half a million descendants.

9
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:37,680
Radiation doesn't kill them.

10
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:39,680
By evolutionary standards,

11
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:42,320
they are nearly
flawless creatures,

12
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,480
but creatures nevertheless.

13
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:48,440
Possessing only
a simple nervous system,

14
00:00:48,520 --> 00:00:54,080
their behavior is dictated solely
by responses to environmental stimuli.

15
00:00:54,160 --> 00:00:58,400
Unlike us, they are
incapable of thought,

16
00:00:58,480 --> 00:01:02,280
of... self-illumination.

17
00:01:04,320 --> 00:01:08,160
Compared to the roach,
we are gods...

18
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:11,080
and must therefore
act accordingly.

19
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:19,040
Is it true if you decapitate them,
they continue to live,

20
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:22,160
eventually dying
of starvation ?

21
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:25,080
Look, buddy,
I just kill 'em.

22
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:32,120
Well, that's why
I called you.

23
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:37,240
I thought that nowadays
you froze the insects to death.

24
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:39,800
Freeze them ?
Where's the fun in that ?

25
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:43,120
No, we got a new pesticide
that works like a fungus.

26
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:45,680
It not only kills
the infected roach,

27
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:47,680
but that roach then
spreads the disease...

28
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:50,000
to every other roach
it comes into contact with.

29
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:54,120
Well, just as long as you,
uh, get rid of them.

30
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:58,960
Bugs-- I don't know.
They drive me crazy.

31
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:05,000
[ Spritzing ]

32
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:10,040
Why, you arrogant little--

33
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,480
[ Chirps ]

34
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:26,240
[ Gasping ]

35
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:30,960
[ Panting ]

36
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,920
[ Screams ]

37
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:52,000
I forgot to tell you
I also found a roach on--

38
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:54,400
[ Groaning ]

39
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:01,680
[Cell Phone Ringing]

40
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:05,600
[Ringing Continues]

41
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:08,720
- Mulder.
- [ Scully] Where have you been ?
I've been trying to reach you.

42
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:13,280
My apartment complex was
being fumigated, so I thought
I'd get away for the weekend.

43
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:15,320
I came up to Massachusetts.

44
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:20,320
- Visiting your mother ?
- No, just, uh, sitting and thinking.

45
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:24,960
Widespread accounts of unidentified
colored lights hovering in the skies...

46
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:28,160
were reported
in this area last night.

47
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:31,440
Look, Scully, I know it's
not your inclination, but...

48
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:33,520
did you ever look up
into the night sky...

49
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:38,240
and feel certain that not only
was something up there, but...

50
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:40,880
it was looking down on you
at that exact same moment...

51
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:45,000
and was just as curious about you
as you are about it ?

52
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:48,120
Mulder, I think the only thing
more fortuitous...

53
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:50,520
than the emergence of life
on this planet is that,

54
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:53,520
through purely random laws
of biological evolution,

55
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:57,240
an intelligence as complex
as ours ever emanated from it.

56
00:04:57,360 --> 00:05:01,040
The very idea of
intelligent alien life...

57
00:05:01,080 --> 00:05:03,480
is not only
astronomically improbable,

58
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:07,280
but, at it's most basic level,
downright anti-Darwinian.

59
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:11,600
Scully,
what are you wearing ?

60
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:15,360
I understand what you’re saying,
but l, I just need to keep looking.

61
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:18,640
Yeah, well, don't look too hard.
You might not like what you find.

62
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:22,960
Isn't that what Dr. Zaius said
to Charlton Heston...

63
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:25,000
at the end of
Planet of the Apes ?

64
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:27,760
And look what happened.

65
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:32,240
- Scully, I got to go.
- What ? Mulder, what's going on ?

66
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:34,440
- [ Dial Tone ]
- Mulder.

67
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:43,400
How you doing ?

68
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:45,840
What are you doing ?

69
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:49,360
-Just sitting, thinking.
- Sitting and thinking ?

70
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:54,080
And talking on the phone ?
Who with, your drug dealer ?
Let me see some I.D.

71
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:03,640
The Bureau ?
You on a case ?

72
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:08,120
I heard reports of several
U.F.O. sightings in this area
last night. You see anything ?

73
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:12,480
No, sir, not personally.
But we did receive
a lot of telephone calls.

74
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:16,040
- Any more calls tonight ?
- No, sir.

75
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:18,080
The F.B.I. keeps tabs
on these things ?

76
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:20,120
No.

77
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:24,040
Excuse me, sir,
I don't like to pry,

78
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:27,120
but why are you sitting here
with your wiper blades on ?

79
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:29,960
Oh, I was just knocking off
some bugs that landed on my--

80
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:34,960
- Landed on my windshield.
- Cockroaches ?

81
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:38,440
Maybe. Maybe beetles.
I don't know.
I'm not really good with bugs.

82
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:41,120
[Woman On Radio]
This is dispatch. Come in. Over.

83
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:54,480
- Sorry to disturb you, sir.
- What's the matter ?

84
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:56,560
Another roach attack.

85
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:02,680
[ Ringing ]

86
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,600
- Hello ?
- I think you better get up here.

87
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:11,560
- What is it ?
- It appears that cockroaches
are mortally attacking people.

88
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:13,600
I'm not gonna ask you if you just said
what I think you just said...

89
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:15,680
because I know
it's what you just said.

90
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:19,000
I'm crouching over a bug exterminator
whose recently deceased body...

91
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:21,960
was discovered with cockroaches
crawling all over him.

92
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:24,640
The local sheriff says
that two other bodies were found...

93
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,720
in the same condition
this afternoon.

94
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:29,240
- Where are you again ?
- Miller's Grove.

95
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:31,200
It has a large
science constituency.

96
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:34,800
The other incidents involved
a molecular biologist
and an astrophysicist,

97
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:38,040
and the witness to this case
is an alternative fuel researcher.

98
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:41,440
These reports are not coming
from yahoos out in the boondocks.

99
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,480
The image
of those cockroaches...

100
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:48,640
has been permanently
imprinted onto my brain.

101
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:51,480
I see them every time
I close my eyes.

102
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:53,600
Try not to close your eyes.

103
00:07:56,120 --> 00:08:00,160
How am I gonna sleep ?
And where ?

104
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:03,480
I'm certainly not
spending the night here.

105
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:06,320
Maybe you could get
a motel room or something.

106
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:09,080
- Were there insect bites on the body ?
- Insect bites ?

107
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,800
- No.
- No.

108
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:14,320
'Cause you know, millions of people
are actually allergic to cockroaches.

109
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,600
There have been reported cases
of fatal reactions.

110
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:19,200
It's called, uh,
anaphylactic shock.

111
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:21,720
- Anaphylactic shock ?
- Mm-hmm. Many such reactions...

112
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:25,240
have occurred to entomologists
or exterminators.

113
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:28,680
- Okay, we'll check that out.
- You still want me to come up ?

114
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:31,760
No, no, no. I'm sure you’re right.
Thanks, Scully.

115
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:34,760
- Who was that ?
- My drug dealer.

116
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:42,800
[Inhaling, Water Bubbling]

117
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:44,880
[ Exhales ]

118
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:49,200
- Dude, that's some good crap.
-[Man Chuckling]

119
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:51,760
Come on, it's your hoot.

120
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:55,040
Um, I don't know about this,
you guys.

121
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:57,080
You really ought to,
you know.

122
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:59,360
Try it.

123
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:02,680
This stuff takes your mind
and just sort of, you know,

124
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:04,800
expands it.

125
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:08,880
Well, something tells me it's
more than my mind you guys
are interested in expanding.

126
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:13,120
Well, how about
another beer then ?

127
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:15,960
- Okay.
- I don't know.

128
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:18,160
I think you’re
making a mistake here.

129
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:21,000
Beer is just, you know,

130
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:23,600
-beer.
- [ Beeps ]

131
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:27,800
But this stuff, it, like,

132
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:30,600
swings the doors
of perception so wide open,

133
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,840
you can see whole
'nother world out there.

134
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:36,600
But it's still like
this world, you know.
It tweaks your mind...

135
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:38,880
and does this whole
altered state thing to it.

136
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:44,320
And suddenly, you see
reality as it, you know,

137
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:46,800
really exists.

138
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:53,800
- Oh, God.
- Dude, what's wrong, man ?

139
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:01,800
Oh, God ! Roaches !

140
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:05,640
- Dude, you're freaking, man !
- Roaches ! Cockroaches !

141
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:07,680
- What's the matter, man ?
- What ?

142
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:12,280
[ Screaming ]

143
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:22,000
[Phone Ringing]

144
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:25,760
- Stay.
- [ Whines ]

145
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,640
-[Ringing Continues]
- Hello.

146
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:31,800
- I take it back, Scully.
I think you better get up here.
- Another roach attack ?

147
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:33,840
Yeah, and this was
no allergic reaction.

148
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:38,400
Two witnesses claim they saw
the victim screaming about
cockroaches burrowing into him.

149
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:40,240
Are there still insects
in the body ?

150
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:43,240
We haven't located any yet,
but there are wounds all over the body.

151
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:45,280
From the cockroaches ?

152
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:49,280
Well, the victim did attempt to extract
the insects using a razor blade,

153
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:51,720
but we're not sure all of
the incisions are self-inflicted,

154
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:53,720
except for the severed artery.

155
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:56,200
Was there any evidence
of drug use at the crime scene ?

156
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:58,800
Uh, well, he did have
a homemade lab set up,

157
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:01,040
but I'm not sure
what he was producing.

158
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:06,120
Aw, man !
Smells like a septic tank !

159
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:08,600
Would you make sure
this gets analyzed here ?

160
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:10,600
You know, Mulder, there's
a psychotic disorder...

161
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:12,600
associated with
some forms of drug abuse...

162
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:16,880
where the abuser suffers from
delusions that insects are
infesting their epidermis.

163
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,920
- It's called Ekbom's Syndrome.
- Ekbom's Syndrome ?

164
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:23,920
The victim cuts himself in an attempt
to extract the imaginary insect.

165
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:25,960
You still want me
to come up ?

166
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:30,560
No. You're probably right.
I'm sorry to bother you.

167
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:33,760
It's no bother. Bye.

168
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:39,000
-[Dog Barking]
- Hey !

169
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:42,080
Kids are brain-dead.
I couldn't get anything out of them.

170
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:44,080
What about some urine ?

171
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:46,200
For a drug test.

172
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:05,000
- Did you get it ?
- Get me a container.

173
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:11,480
Oh, I think I killed it.

174
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:13,520
[Sheriff] You killed it ?
You annihilated it.

175
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:16,920
It must have molted.
It’s just empty exoskeleton.

176
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,800
Well, at least we have evidence
that cockroaches were actually here.

177
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:22,360
We've got more
than that, Sheriff.

178
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:24,680
I think that bug's exoskeleton
was made of metal.

179
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,480
Nothing more than
a skin abrasion.

180
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,560
An abrasion caused by
a metallic substance ?

181
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:46,240
Why don't we wait until the analysis
of the compound is finished...

182
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,600
before jumping
to any conclusions ?

183
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:55,160
Uh, Agent Mulder, as a doctor,
I always find it best to be...

184
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:57,600
completely honest and
open with my patients,

185
00:12:57,720 --> 00:13:00,040
no matter how unpleasant
the information.

186
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:02,600
What do you need
to tell me ?

187
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:04,960
No. I need you
to tell me something.

188
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,920
What the hell
is going on here ?

189
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:11,200
Wha--

190
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:15,000
- Are we in any danger ?
- I don't know.

191
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:18,800
- Well, should I evacuate my family ?
- I wouldn't know.

192
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:22,160
Doc, they're waiting for you
to examine the boy's body.

193
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:25,600
Yeah, uh, as soon I
take a little break.

194
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:30,120
After talking with Agent Mulder here,
I suddenly feel slightly constipated.

195
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:37,520
- What's his problem ?
- He's upset that I don't know
what's going on here.

196
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,360
So what the hell
is going on here ?

197
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:46,920
[ Beeps ]

198
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:16,520
I see the correlation, but just because
I work for the federal government...

199
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:18,640
doesn't mean I'm an expert
on cockroaches.

200
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:21,360
So you don't know anything about
the government's experiments...

201
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:23,960
- being conducted here ?
- Experiments ?

202
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:26,600
A couple of months ago,
an agent claiming to be from
the Department of Agriculture...

203
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:29,400
sets up base on
a couple of acres across town.

204
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:32,760
Nobody knows exactly
what's going on out there.

205
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:36,040
- It's top secret, very hush-hush.
- What are you suggesting ?

206
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:40,280
Killer bees were
a genetic experiment gone awry,

207
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:43,280
let loose on
an unsuspecting populace.

208
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:48,240
Who's to say the government
hasn't created a new breed
of killer cockroaches ?

209
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:50,680
You might want to keep that theory
to yourself, Sheriff.

210
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:52,800
No need to create a panic.

211
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:56,880
[Man] Oh!Oh, my God!
Help! Somebody help! Hey!

212
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:00,840
What the hell happened ?

213
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:04,160
Cockroaches.
He was covered in cockroaches.

214
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:08,400
- I don't see any roaches.
- When I went out to look
for help and I came back,

215
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:11,840
they disappeared.

216
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:27,720
Gently. Gently.

217
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:35,080
Hmm. Doesn't appear odd
in any-- Ooh !

218
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,520
[ Beeps ]

219
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:42,840
Next time,
let me handle the roaches.

220
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:46,080
[ Ringing ]

221
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:50,600
- Who died now ?
- The medical examiner.

222
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:53,560
His body was found next to a toilet,
covered with roaches.

223
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:57,360
- I really think you should come--
- A toilet ? Check his eyes.

224
00:15:57,400 --> 00:16:00,080
Is one of them bloodshot
with a dilated pupil ?

225
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:05,200
- Yeah.
- Well, it's probably
a brain aneurysm.

226
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:08,160
- Brain aneurysm ?
- Straining too forcefully...

227
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:10,840
is very common causation
for bursting a brain aneurysm.

228
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:13,520
Well, how do you
explain the roaches though ?

229
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:16,840
- Did you catch any ?
- Almost.

230
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:18,840
I don't know
what to tell you, Mulder.

231
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:21,240
I just hope you’re not implying
you've come across an infestation...

232
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:24,120
of killer cockroaches.

233
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:30,640
[Cell Phone Ringing]

234
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:34,440
- Mulder.
- [ Scully] Mulder ?

235
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:36,560
I've been doing some research.

236
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:40,320
Back in the mid-'80s,
there was a cockroach species
previously only found in Asia,

237
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:42,440
and since then, it's made
an appearance in Florida.

238
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:45,320
They've now completely established
themselves in this country.

239
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:49,800
- Do they attack people ?
- No, but they exhibit behavior
different than domestic breeds.

240
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:52,480
They fly for long distances,
and they're attracted to light.

241
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:56,040
- But do they attack people ?
- I'm suggesting that what's
happening out there...

242
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:59,120
might be the introduction
to this country of a new
species of cockroach,

243
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:02,640
- one that is attracted to people.
- That all makes perfect sense, Scully.

244
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:03,880
I don't like it at all.
Did you know that
the federal government,

245
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:06,680
under the guise of
the Department of Agriculture,

246
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:09,040
has been conducting
secret experiments up here ?

247
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:12,360
You're not thinking about
trespassing onto government
property again, are you ?

248
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:15,040
I know that you’ve done it
in the past, but I don't think
that this case warrants--

249
00:17:15,120 --> 00:17:17,360
It's too late.
I'm already inside.

250
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:19,360
[ Sighs ]

251
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:22,480
Well, what's going on ?
What do you see ?

252
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:24,520
I'm in a house.

253
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:27,280
It's apparently empty.

254
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:30,400
- What does the place look like ?
- It's a, uh...

255
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:33,680
typical two-story suburban house.

256
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:36,000
Nice big living room,
sparsely furnished.

257
00:17:36,080 --> 00:17:38,800
Nice carpets, fireplace.

258
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:41,040
Nice kitchen.

259
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:43,600
Modern appliances.

260
00:17:45,560 --> 00:17:48,960
- Moving walls.
- Moving walls ?

261
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:53,680
Yeah. They're rippling.

262
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:58,720
Oh ! Cockroaches !

263
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:02,600
- What ?
- Cockroaches. They're everywhere.

264
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:08,160
Ah ! I'm surrounded !

265
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:10,200
Mulder, you've got to
get out of there right now.

266
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:13,000
- Nooo !
- Are you all right ? What happened ?

267
00:18:13,080 --> 00:18:15,680
Flashlight went out.

268
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:19,680
Mulder, what's going on ?

269
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:22,320
Gotta go.

270
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:24,440
Mulder ! Mulder !

271
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:27,600
[ Dial Tone ]

272
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:33,520
May I ask why you're trespassing
on government property ?

273
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:36,080
- I'm a federal agent.
- So am l.

274
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:38,120
Agent Mulder, F.B.I.

275
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:42,400
Doctor Berenbaum, U.S.D.A.
Agricultural Research Service.

276
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:45,440
Doctor Berenbaum, I'm going to
have to ask you a few questions.

277
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:48,040
For instance ?

278
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:50,720
What's a woman like you
doing in a place like this ?

279
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:57,920
By studying how insects
respond to changes in light,

280
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,880
temperature, air currents,
food availability,

281
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:03,360
we can determine the best ways
to eradicate them.

282
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:05,440
Why all the secrecy
about your research ?

283
00:19:05,520 --> 00:19:08,480
You've got some of
the good townspeople suspicious.

284
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:10,720
You expect us to advertise
that we've intentionally...

285
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:14,520
infested a house in their neighborhood
with thousands of cockroaches ?

286
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:18,680
But those, those cockroaches,
are they a normal species ?

287
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:20,920
They're a common one.

288
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:26,680
Have you ever come across a type of
cockroach that is attracted to people ?

289
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:30,920
Most cockroaches have been known
to actually wash themselves...

290
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,120
- after being touched by humans.
- Really.

291
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:36,360
So you’ve never seen
an instance where a cockroach
actually attacks a human being ?

292
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:41,080
There have been cases where a cockroach
has crawled into a person's ear or nose.

293
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,160
Nose ?

294
00:19:45,080 --> 00:19:47,360
What is that there ?

295
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:49,640
Oh, it’s just
a pet project of mine.

296
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:53,440
Since an insect's exoskeleton
is a dielectric...

297
00:19:53,520 --> 00:19:57,960
surrounding the conductive
medium of its body fluid,

298
00:19:58,040 --> 00:20:00,000
when introduced into
an electrical field,

299
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:02,640
the brushed discharge will
result in a colored fare.

300
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:07,640
What is that
supposed to prove ?

301
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:12,880
Well, it's my theory that U.F.O.'s
are actually insect swarms.

302
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:15,160
I don't know if you know
anything about U.F.O.'s,

303
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:18,280
but all the characteristics
of a typical sighting...

304
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:20,320
are shared with
nocturnal insects...

305
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:22,520
swarming through
an electrical air field.

306
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:26,800
The sudden appearance
of a colored, glowing light
hovering in the night sky,

307
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:30,120
moving in a nonmechanical
matter, possibly humming,

308
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:33,280
creating interference with
radio and television signals,

309
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:35,600
then suddenly disappearing.

310
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:40,360
As, uh,
nocturnal insect swarms,

311
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:43,080
that's, uh, that's fascinating.

312
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:46,560
Everything about insects
is fascinating.

313
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:49,320
They are truly
remarkable creatures.

314
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:53,640
- So beautiful and so honest.
- Honest ?

315
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:58,320
Eat, sleep,
defecate, procreate.

316
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:00,840
That's all they do.
That's all we do,

317
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:04,880
but at least insects
don't kid themselves that
it's anything more than that.

318
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:08,600
Does my scientific
detachment disturb you ?

319
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:13,080
No. No, actually, l,
I find it quite refreshing.

320
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:16,080
[Cell Phone Ringing]

321
00:21:17,960 --> 00:21:21,240
Not now. You know, um--

322
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:27,400
I have always found insects
to be very interesting.

323
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:29,520
Really ?

324
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:37,760
This is the fifth report
of a deceased body...

325
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:39,840
being found amongst
a horde of cockroaches,

326
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:43,000
but police are not confirming,
at least not yet,

327
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:46,600
that the insects have anything
to do with the fatalities.

328
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,960
Police have also disaffirmed the rumor
that these deaths were the result...

329
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:51,120
of an outbreak
of the Ebola virus...

330
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:54,120
somehow being spread
by infected cockroaches.

331
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:57,400
As for now, these incidents remain
under local jurisdiction,

332
00:21:57,480 --> 00:22:01,920
but a nurse here did confirm
that an F.B.I. agent is on the case.

333
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:05,720
Police are asking that if you see
any cockroaches, don't panic.

334
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:10,600
Simply notify the local authorities
and evacuate the area immediately.

335
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:13,960
Reporting live, this is Skye Leikin
for Channel Three, Night watch News.

336
00:22:14,040 --> 00:22:17,160
Then suddenly,
there was this terrible crash.

337
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:19,160
You know,
you could've been killed.

338
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:36,000
[ Blowing Nose ]

339
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:55,280
- [ Ringing ]
- Mulder, are you okay ?

340
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:58,320
- I can't sleep.
- What happened at the U.S.D.A. site ?

341
00:22:58,360 --> 00:23:00,800
They're conducting
legitimate experiments.

342
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:03,760
I met an entomologist,
Dr. Berenbaum,

343
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:07,760
who agrees with your theory
of an accidental importation
of a new cockroach species.

344
00:23:07,840 --> 00:23:09,920
Did he give you any idea
of how to catch them ?

345
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:13,960
No. But she did tell me
everything else there is
to know about insects.

346
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:17,520
- She ?
- Yeah. Did you know
that the ancient Egyptians...

347
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:20,880
worshipped the scarab beetle
and possibly erected the pyramids...

348
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:24,520
to honor them, which may just be
giant symbolic dung heaps ?

349
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:28,800
Did you know the inventor
of the flush toilet
was named Thomas Crapper ?

350
00:23:28,880 --> 00:23:31,720
- Bambi also has this theory
I've never come acro--
- Who ?

351
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:35,720
- Dr. Berenbaum.
Anyway, her theory is--
- Her name is Bambi ?

352
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:38,800
Yeah. Both her parents
were naturalists.

353
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:42,440
Her theory is that U.F.O.'s are
actually nocturnal insect swarms...

354
00:23:42,520 --> 00:23:44,560
passing through
electrical air fields.

355
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:49,120
- Her name is Bambi ?
- Scully, can I confess
something to you ?

356
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:51,680
Yeah, sure, okay.

357
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:54,040
I hate insects.

358
00:23:54,120 --> 00:23:56,560
You know, lots of people
are afraid of insects, Mulder.

359
00:23:56,640 --> 00:24:00,240
It’s just a--
It's a natural, instinctive--

360
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:02,800
No, no, I'm not afraid of them.

361
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:05,400
I hate them.

362
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:08,720
One day back when
I was a kid, I was, uh,

363
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:12,440
I was climbing this tree when I noticed
this leaf walking towards me.

364
00:24:12,520 --> 00:24:14,440
It took forever to realize
that it was no leaf.

365
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:17,720
- A praying mantis ?
- Yeah, I had
a praying mantis epiphany.

366
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:21,600
And as a result, I screamed.
No, not a girlie scream,

367
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:24,680
but the scream of someone
being confronted by some
before unknown monster...

368
00:24:24,800 --> 00:24:28,240
that had no right existing
on the same planet I inhabited.

369
00:24:28,320 --> 00:24:32,520
Did you ever notice
how a praying mantis' head
resembles an alien's head ?

370
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:35,520
The mysteries of the natural world
were revealed to me that day,

371
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,760
but instead of
being astounded, I was...

372
00:24:37,840 --> 00:24:40,120
- repulsed.
- Mulder,

373
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:42,280
are you sure
it wasn't a girlie scream ?

374
00:24:42,360 --> 00:24:44,600
- [Man Screaming]
- What was that ?

375
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:48,400
- Oh, I got to go.
- Mul-- No-- Ohh !

376
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:53,040
- Did you hear that too ?
- Came from over there.

377
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:57,760
What the hell's going on ?

378
00:24:57,840 --> 00:25:00,800
Hello ?

379
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:02,760
Is everything
all right in there ?

380
00:25:08,720 --> 00:25:12,040
[Screaming]

381
00:25:18,760 --> 00:25:20,720
Don't go in there, man !

382
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:40,240
[Phone Ringing]

383
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:45,240
What happened this time ?

384
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:47,480
One of the motel guests died.

385
00:25:47,560 --> 00:25:49,960
Mulder, I'm coming up there
right now.

386
00:25:50,040 --> 00:25:53,920
Scully, I think this man died simply
from a reaction to the cockroaches.

387
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:55,920
Two cases
of anaphylactic shock...

388
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:58,720
in the same day in the same town
is highly improbable.

389
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:03,440
No. I'm saying that I think
this man simply had a heart attack.

390
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:05,600
Word about
the cockroach infestation...

391
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:07,800
and the deaths related to it
has gotten out,

392
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:12,440
and I think this man simply saw some
cockroaches and scared himself to death.

393
00:26:12,520 --> 00:26:17,080
- Regardless, Mulder, something
strange is going on out there.
- Maybe not.

394
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:19,680
All your conjectures
have proved correct.

395
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:23,000
The exterminator did die
from anaphylactic shock.

396
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:25,520
The teenage boy did die
from self-inflicted wounds...

397
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:29,560
and was getting high off methane fumes
derived from burning manure.

398
00:26:29,640 --> 00:26:32,440
The medical examiner did die
from a brain aneurysm.

399
00:26:32,520 --> 00:26:35,520
I still haven't been able to explain
the cockroaches at all these sites.

400
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:38,720
Or the fact that their exoskeletons
are made of metal.

401
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:42,200
Metal ? What are you
talking about ?

402
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:45,440
Mulder ? Mulder,
I'm coming up there.

403
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:47,600
Whatever.

404
00:26:56,760 --> 00:27:00,680
- Can you tell
what kind of cockroach it is ?
- I should be able to.

405
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:04,680
The abdomen's still attached,
and we differentiate species
by their genitalia.

406
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:08,640
- Oh, my God.
- Is it abnormal ?

407
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:13,280
I'll say. He's hung like
a club-tailed dragonfly.
Excuse me.

408
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:21,240
Does it still look unusual ?

409
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:24,880
Well, yes,
for an insect genitalia,

410
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:27,520
but maybe not
for a microprocessor.

411
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:29,680
You're implying that
this insect is mechanical ?

412
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:35,600
What am I supposed
to be looking at here ?

413
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:38,400
Have you ever seen
anything like this before ?

414
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:41,160
Only in science journals.

415
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:43,840
I've read about
an artificial intelligence researcher...

416
00:27:43,920 --> 00:27:47,160
who designs robots that resemble
and behave like insects.

417
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:51,200
I've never seen them myself, but I've
often thought of visiting his lab.

418
00:27:51,280 --> 00:27:53,840
He works out of this town ?

419
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:11,360
[ Whirring ]

420
00:28:30,040 --> 00:28:33,320
[Whirring]

421
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:37,800
- Doctor Ivanov ?
- Why are you scaring my robots ?

422
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:41,680
For decades, my colleagues
in artificial intelligence...

423
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:45,880
have attempted to create
an autonomous robot.

424
00:28:45,960 --> 00:28:48,000
By struggling
to give their machines...

425
00:28:48,080 --> 00:28:50,760
a human-like brain,
they have failed.

426
00:28:50,840 --> 00:28:55,080
A human brain is too complex,
too computational.

427
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:57,760
It thinks too much.

428
00:28:57,840 --> 00:29:02,280
But insects merely react.

429
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:06,680
I use insects as my model,

430
00:29:06,800 --> 00:29:12,120
not just in design but by giving them
the simplest of computer programs.

431
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:16,240
"Go to the object.
Go away from moving object. "

432
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:19,480
Governed only by sensors
and reflex responses,

433
00:29:19,560 --> 00:29:23,080
they take on the behavior
of intelligent living beings.

434
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:26,440
So this one is just programmed
to head towards any object...

435
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:28,800
moving within the field
of its sensors ?

436
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:31,440
No.

437
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:33,640
Then why is it
following me ?

438
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:37,080
It likes you.

439
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:40,520
Your contract is with NASA ?

440
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:43,120
The goal is to transport
a fleet of robots...

441
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:46,760
to another planet and allow them
to navigate the terrain...

442
00:29:46,840 --> 00:29:51,440
with more intricacy than
any space probe has done before.

443
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:53,680
It sounds slightly fantastic,

444
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:56,120
but the only obstacle
I can foresee...

445
00:29:56,200 --> 00:29:59,120
is devising a renewable
energy source.

446
00:29:59,240 --> 00:30:03,760
In any case, this is the future
of space exploration.

447
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:06,840
It does not include
living entities.

448
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:10,920
I'm just speculating here, but if
extraterrestrial life-forms do exist--

449
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:13,320
Oh, there's no need for speculation.
I believe they do.

450
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:15,560
And assuming that they're more
technologically advanced than we are,

451
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:19,280
and if your own ideas about the future
of space exploration are correct, then--

452
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:22,800
Then the interplanetary
explorers of alien civilizations...

453
00:30:22,880 --> 00:30:25,240
will likely be
mechanical in nature.

454
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:28,440
Yes. Anyone who thinks
alien visitation...

455
00:30:28,520 --> 00:30:30,720
will come
not in the form of robots,

456
00:30:30,800 --> 00:30:34,960
but of living beings
with big eyes and gray skin...

457
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:38,520
has been brainwashed by
too much science fiction.

458
00:30:46,520 --> 00:30:51,360
- Can you identify this ?
- I'm not really good with bugs.

459
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:54,720
- A cricket's leg ?
- Try it under the microscope.

460
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:19,800
Are you all right,
Dr. Ivanov ?

461
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:24,680
Can you identify that ?

462
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:27,480
[ No Audio Dialogue ]

463
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:29,640
Sir ?

464
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:37,440
It's... beyond my comprehension.

465
00:31:41,840 --> 00:31:44,200
Hey, kid, move it !
Gimme that !

466
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:46,600
[ Yelling ]

467
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:53,240
[Man]
Back off, buddy!

468
00:31:54,960 --> 00:31:57,440
Get it ! Hurry up !

469
00:31:57,560 --> 00:31:59,560
- Get your own !
- I saw it first !

470
00:31:59,680 --> 00:32:02,720
[Yelling Continues]

471
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:08,320
[ Tires Screeching ]

472
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:12,040
[Man Shouting]
Hey, what are you, crazy ?
Why are you stopping ?

